items.synopsis: The FIFA Women's World Cup round of 16 gets underway with sixth-ranked Spain taking on Switzerland in Auckland. Later, Japan takes on Norway in Wellington. Follow live.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Emphatic performance from Spain, coming off their 4-0 loss to Japan in the group stage. They cruise into the quarter-finals, and look a formidable opponent for anyone. It wasn't just the scoreline, it was the way they played - barely giving Switzerland a look at the ball. And their problems in front of goal have been solved, for now at least, registering 26 shots to 2, and showing some real flair and precision in the box.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL-TIME: Switzerland 1 - 5 Spain

children.content: Emphatic performance from Spain, coming off their 4-0 loss to Japan in the group stage.
They cruise into the quarter-finals, and look a formidable opponent for anyone.

It wasn't just the scoreline, it was the way they played - barely giving Switzerland a look at the ball. And their problems in front of goal have been solved, for now at least, registering 26 shots to 2, and showing some real flair and precision in the box.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Switzerland give it away trying to play out from left back. Hermoso receives it in heaps of space and has no trouble guiding it past the keeper. The match had been in a bit of a lull, but Switzerland's mistake has allowed Spain to increase their lead.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: 70' GOAL Hermoso - five of the best from Spain

children.content: Switzerland give it away trying to play out from left back. Hermoso receives it in heaps of space and has no trouble guiding it past the keeper.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Scintillating Spain! Absolutely imperial performance from the Spanish, coming off their 4-0 loss to Germany. Everything went right for them - barring that shocking own goal. Aitana Bonmati has been immense, scoring two and setting another up.
